<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idd2b192dd-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5" identifier="/us/usc/t47/s765c"><num value="765c">§ 765c.</num><heading> ITU functions</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idd2b192de-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5" identifier="/us/usc/t47/s765c/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Technical coordination</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Commission and United States satellite companies shall utilize the International Telecommunication Union procedures for technical coordination with INTELSAT and its successor entities and separated entities, rather than INTELSAT procedures.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idd2b192df-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5" identifier="/us/usc/t47/s765c/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> ITU notifying administration</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The President and the Commission shall take the action necessary to ensure that the United States remains the ITU notifying administration for the privatized INTELSAT’s existing and future orbital slot registrations.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idd2b192e0-4ef6-11f1-9110-db228fde61c5">(<ref href="/us/pl/87/624/tVI/s644">Pub. L. 87–624, title VI, § 644</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/106/180/s3">Pub. L. 106–180, § 3</ref>, <date date="2000-03-17">Mar. 17, 2000</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/114/56">114 Stat. 56</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
